<p>I need to make a PDF generator using TCPDF and PHP. I could just write everything on the PDF, but that would look awful. Therefore, I need to get every product in the HTML on a different page.</p>  <p>With the newer pages, it's pretty easy. Just use dom document to find the <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> around the products, put it in an array and write that to the PDF.</p>  <p>Unfortunately, not every page is the same, so not every page has <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>. This page for example.</p>  <pre><code>'&lt;h3&gt;sample#1&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;img&gt; &lt;table&gt; &lt;/table&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;sample#2&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Aenean commodo ligula eget dolor. Aenean massa.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;img&gt; &lt;table&gt; &lt;/table&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;sample#3&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cum sociis natoque penatibus et magnis dis parturient montes, nascetur ridiculus mus.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;img&gt; &lt;table&gt; &lt;/table&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;sample#4&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Donec quam felis, ultricies nec, pellentesque eu, pretium quis, sem.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;img&gt; &lt;table&gt; &lt;/table&gt;' </code></pre>  <p>So what I'm trying to get, is something like this:</p>  <pre><code>array (size=4) 0 =&gt; string " &lt;h3&gt;sample#1&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;img&gt; &lt;table&gt; &lt;/table&gt;" 1=&gt; string " &lt;h3&gt;sample#2&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Aenean commodo ligula eget dolor. Aenean massa.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;img&gt; &lt;table&gt; &lt;/table&gt;" </code></pre>  <p>etc.</p>  <p>I have no problem with including something into the server files if needed, but preferably not.</p>